  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Confirmed asthma within the past 2 years (12% bronchodilator reversibility or PC20
             methacholine less than 8 mg/ml)

          -  Sputum eosinophils greater than 3% on at least 2 occasions

          -  Asthma Control Questionnaire (ACQ) &lt;1.5 and sputum eos &lt;3% at the time of
             randomization (ie. optimal steroid dose)

          -  On Inhaled corticosteroids (ICS) and Long acting beta agonist (LABA) (irrespective of
             dose)

          -  Total serum IgE &gt;120 IU/L

          -  Age between 18 and 75 years

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Current smoker or ex-smokers with greater than 20 pack years

          -  Co-morbid diseases which in the investigator's opinion would make the patient
             unsuitable to participate in the study

          -  Currently on Omalizumab or has previously been treated with Omalizumab

          -  Currently on other biologic therapies

          -  Pregnancy or lactation

          -  Post bronchodilator FEV1 less than 50% predicted
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
